tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE CADFiles (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    file_name VARCHAR(255),
    file_path VARCHAR(255),
    upload_date TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE print_logs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    print_status VARCHAR(50),
    printer_name VARCHAR(100),
    date_printed TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE CADFiles (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    file_name VARCHAR(255),
    file_size INT,
    uploaded_by VARCHAR(100),
    uploaded_at TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE PrintJobs (
    job_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    CAD_file_id INT,
    printer_id INT,
    job_status VARCHAR(50),
    job_started_at TIMESTAMP,
    job_completed_at TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (CAD_file_id) REFERENCES CADFiles(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (printer_id) REFERENCES Printers(printer_id)
);

CREATE TABLE model_parts (
    part_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT NOT NULL,
    part_name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,
    part_file_path VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (model_id) REFERENCES cad_models(id)
);

CREATE TABLE printing_history (
    print_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT NOT NULL,
    print_date DATE NOT NULL,
    print_status VARCHAR(20) NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (model_id) REFERENCES cad_models(id)
);

CREATE TABLE printer_settings (
    setting_id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT NOT NULL,
    layer_height FLOAT NOT NULL,
    print_speed INT NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (model_id) REFERENCES cad_models(id)
);

CREATE TABLE print_jobs (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    model_id INT,
    printer_id INT,
    material_id INT,
    date_requested DATE,
    date_completed DATE,
    status VARCHAR(50)
);
